### Describe the bug

Injecting a bean like this one:
```
public class BeanParam
{
	private String stringValue;
	private long longValue;	
	@QueryParam("string-value")
	public void setStringValue(String stringValue)
	{
		this.stringValue = stringValue;
	}
	@QueryParam("long-value")
	public void setLongValue(long longValue)
	{
		this.longValue = longValue;
	}
}
```
as endpoint parameter with `@BeanParam` causes an HTTP error 404 due to a `ClassCastException`.

The bean slightly modified
```
public class BeanParam
{
	@QueryParam("_unused")
	private String _unused;
	private String stringValue;
	private long longValue;
	
	@QueryParam("string-value")
	public void setStringValue(String stringValue)
	{
		this.stringValue = stringValue;
	}
...
``` 
doesn't produce the `ClassCastException`, but `@QueryParam` annotations are not honored.

### Expected behavior

Bean injected with extracted values from query string

### Actual behavior

```
